suckers wild smile these guys are a
Brooklyn quartet and this is their debut
full-length with a creepy-ass baboon on
the front now my first introduction to
this band was a little EP that just blew
me away on first listen with just
several tracks on it but they were
really good several tracks including
songs that I'm sure you guys can find
out about online beach queen and it gets
your body moving and I caught sounds on
that EP that were reminding me of
talking heads Modest Mouse some
post-punk stuff and a little bit of
post-rock too I mean ya suckers were on
that release incorporating a lot of
different sounds a lot of different
ideas but they were also well-placed
which is hard to find so because of that
I'm excited to hear these guys do it
full length style and hear them really
explore their strangeness explore their
pop sensibilities to their limit

brought the best elements of that EP to
this full-length ambitious song
structures really shimmering production
giant sing-along choruses and some
